title: Average regular season home attendance of the Tennessee Titans 2008 to 2019
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Average attendance, with a total of 12 data points. The chart has 3 significant trends.
The longest trend is slightly neutral which exists from 2015 to 2008.
Also, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2019 to 2017.
Conversely, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2017 to 2015.
gold: This graph depicts the average regular season home attendance of the Tennessee Titans from 2008 to 2019 . In 2019 , the average attendance at home games of the Tennessee Titans was 64,509 .
